{"org":"Cannock Chase","wards":[{"ward":"Brereton & Ravenhill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":33.1,"results_url":"https://www.cannockchasedc.gov.uk/council/elections-voting/elections/election-results/cannock-chase-district-council-elections-7-may","candidates":[{"n":"Michael Sheppard","p":"Reform UK","v":1111,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"131864","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/131864/93b35f0b-5fce-481a-981d-a1e68851bef9.png"},{"n":"Dave Williams","p":"Labour and Co-operative Party","v":500,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"101225","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/101225/cc3ec3f0-ea07-495a-9803-7b75148b093b.png","stmt":"**I am Dave Williams, Labour and Co-operative candidate for Brereton and Ravenhill. I have served this ward as a District Councillor since 2023, and I am asking for your vote on Thursday 7 May to continue that work.**\n\nBefore entering local politics I served in the Royal Marines and worked as an NHS physiotherapist. I bring that background to my role as Portfolio Holder for Community Wellbeing and as the council's Armed Forces Champion.\n\nIn the last three years I have secured £2.3 million of investment in local leisure facilities, £1.4 million for homelessness prevention, and £140,000 for Flaxley Park. I have kept Chase Leisure Centre and Rugeley Leisure Centre open under a new ten-year contract with no borrowing required. As Armed Forces Champion I have built real links with our local reserve units - bringing civic pride and resilience into the heart of how this council works.\n\nBrereton and Ravenhill has three Labour councillors who work as a team. Together we get more done.\n\nThis vote is not about Westminster. It is about your leisure centre, your park, your street. I do not make promises I cannot keep. Three years of results - and more still to do.\n\n**Service. Community. Results.**","bd":"1989"},{"n":"Keeren Joseph Hart","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":288,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"109986","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/109986/11471180-cba4-4623-939e-d84a495f1bc2.png"},{"n":"Ian John Pyke","p":"Green Party","v":268,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"74924","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/74924/cde37208-1bee-4603-b984-805fa4c22a19.png"}]},{"ward":"Cannock Longford & Bridgtown","seats":1,"turnout_pct":37.28,"results_url":"https://www.cannockchasedc.gov.uk/council/elections-voting/elections/election-results/cannock-chase-district-council-elections-7-may","candidates":[{"n":"Richard James Craddock","p":"Reform UK","v":1378,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109991","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/109991/0feb92aa-6c48-4431-a960-8dffe371f495.png"},{"n":"Doug Smith","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":441,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"10101","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/10101/31934f77-a5fe-497a-bdb6-f0e7d135ec90.png"},{"n":"Denise Elizabeth Gold","p":"Labour Party","v":400,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"126588","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/126588/9c4b70ee-304b-4fc2-83ff-c2472a158b75.png","stmt":"I'm Denise Gold, standing for Labour in Cannock, Longford and Bridgtown. I've lived in Cannock  for over 50 years. I've worked for local government for over 35 years as well as for  Staffordshire Wildlife Trust; passionate about animal welfare, environmental concerns supporting wildlife and their habitats . If elected I will hold the council to account, scrutinise its decisions, work with the council’s partners to build a new vibrant town centre and engage with local policing to find and address the root causes of anti social behaviour."},{"n":"Eloise Siobhan Cropp","p":"Green Party","v":346,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"39131","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/120768/4e7ac97b-378e-4f51-bb60-f25cb93170cc.png","stmt":"I live with my family in Cannock and I work as a teaching assistant. \nI use and actively support our local businesses, public transport and community facilities.\nI want to make sure Cannock Chase is a safe and welcoming place for children to grow up."},{"n":"Gareth Knox","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":23,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"81040","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/81040/e2bdd972-5f12-429c-9f65-c1a7719ad2cc.png"}]},{"ward":"Cannock Park & Old Fallow","seats":1,"turnout_pct":41.49,"results_url":"https://www.cannockchasedc.gov.uk/council/elections-voting/elections/election-results/cannock-chase-district-council-elections-7-may","candidates":[{"n":"Mandy Jane Bell","p":"Reform UK","v":1467,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128279","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128279/1c128d19-3f1d-44bf-b95d-7d94efd95e4b.png"},{"n":"Paris Theodorou","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":594,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"88066","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/88066/7d94b953-09bc-44f7-8499-dbfc5054cd73.png","tw":"\"ParisTheodorou\""},{"n":"Steven Thornley","p":"Labour Party","v":349,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"88083","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/88083/73f1eb83-c609-41e0-a927-406c3a99e1b6.png"},{"n":"Warren Simon Cocker","p":"Green Party","v":282,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"66830","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/66830/41fe0f14-0c24-491d-ac67-b553bc11f