false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"65861","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/65861/89f32004-29c8-4091-a898-41c4adbd29a4.png","stmt":"Here's some info about me...... I currently live in Etching Hill and I have lived in Rugeley for the whole of my life.\n\nHaving been a District Councillor in the past, I understand what is needed to really represent our community and to stand up for residents. As a Councillor I was known for resolving issues raised by residents, holding local ‘help and advice’ sessions and carrying out ‘estate walks’ on the Springfields to identify and report issues.\n\nBy working with residents, together we addressed numerous issues in the area such as fly-tipping, housing repairs and overgrown trees and hedges.\n\nI have lived in the area all my life and understand the challenges we have faced as a community over recent years, such as unemployment and deteriorating public amenities.\n\nSupporting the community is important to me, advocating for residents’ concerns and supporting initiatives to help resolve the problems we face.\n\nIf elected, I aim to focus on listening, learning, and building constructive relationships – I recognise that people in the community often have the best solutions to problems, and that long-term success is achieved through co-operation and shared purpose.\n\nMy approach is guided by a focus on transparency, fairness, and practical outcomes to support strong communities and ensuring that people feel informed, respected and included in the processes that affect them.\n\nKey Achievements\n\nContributed to community initiatives focused on improving local services and resident wellbeing, including promoting healthy cooking sessions and sharing energy saving ideas and initiatives.\nWorked collaboratively with organisations to address neighbourhood priorities such as anti-social behaviour.\nPromoted council transparency, by clearly explaining why decisions were being made and sharing this with residents, for example planning outcomes and budget announcements.\nChampioned practical, sustainable solutions shaped by residents’ feedback, including securing Council‑funded skips for ","bd":"1967"},{"n":"Diane Lynette Phizacklea","p":"Green Party","v":294,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"131930","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/131930/3d54bbbf-675e-4f39-98aa-fd07c2f6d532.png"}]},{"ward":"Hawks Green with Rumer Hill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":39.54,"results_url":"https://www.cannockchasedc.gov.uk/council/elections-voting/elections/election-results/cannock-chase-district-council-elections-7-may","candidates":[{"n":"Melissa Kirsty Cecil","p":"Reform UK","v":1178,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128316","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128316/db7eb8d2-7075-4382-8dc6-11df2b5e8b9f.png"},{"n":"Phil Hewitt","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":611,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"10087","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/10087/df93f474-6e28-4a43-893b-cf03bf9becff.png"},{"n":"Kevin Gary Elson","p":"Green Party","v":293,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"109985"},{"n":"Leslie William Bullock","p":"Labour Party","v":271,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"39148","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/39148/f98a5615-cf25-4669-b048-d6189a5c2ca4.png"}]},{"ward":"Heath Hayes & Wimblebury","seats":1,"turnout_pct":37.44,"results_url":"https://www.cannockchasedc.gov.uk/council/elections-voting/elections/election-results/cannock-chase-district-council-elections-7-may","candidates":[{"n":"Daniel Paul Cecil","p":"Reform UK","v":1468,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"121683","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/121683/972686bc-5242-4